    {
      "id": "sybil_11_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_11",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera is a superlative example of the 996.2 chassis. The 3.6L flat-six powerplant is paired with a 6-speed manual transaxle, featuring a proactive ceramic IMS bearing upgrade and a documented rear main seal replacement. The factory M030 sport suspension provides exceptional lateral stability, while the braking system utilizes cross-drilled rotors with four-piston monobloc calipers for fade-free deceleration. A recent DME interrogation confirms zero overrevs in upper ranges, validating the mechanical integrity of the valvetrain. The exterior retains its original factory-applied finish with zero evidence of track-use pitting or panel misalignment. Inside, the cabin remains hermetically preserved with supple leather and a crisp, short-throw shifter. This is a mechanically sorted, collector-quality specimen for the serious enthusiast.",
